parameters:
Leader of the Loparo Plundering Gang: Welcome to the near-
death Loparo Plundering Gang hideout.

Loparo Plundering Gang Leader: The fact that you guys have
come means that both the Imperial Army and the Pido know our
whereabouts.

Sister Eleo: I am Sister Eleo, a priestess. I have come
today to speak with you.
Sister Eleo: Please tell me your name.

Loparo Plundering Gang Leader: Have you come to give us a
sermon, oh holy priestess, even though I have abandoned my
name on the battlefield?

Sister Eleo: Please do not commit any more sins. Let us go
together to the guards of the campus.

Loparo Plundering Gang Leader: There's no way the Pido, who
have [annihilated] more than half of our comrades, will let
us off with just a hanging.

Loparo Plundering Gang Leader: Are you telling me, holy
priestess, to go and die?

Loparo Plundering Gang Leader: Praying and preaching is just
an easy job. Prostitutes have a much more respectable
business.
Sister Eleo: So you think prayer has no value?

Loparo Plundering Gang Leader: That's how it is. I'm
different from you, I can't understand. Isn't that enough?

Loparo Plundering Gang Leader: Well, the conversation is
over. I believe it is necessary to kill all the witnesses.
Loparo Plundering Gang Leader: Will the others resist?

Sister Sophia: Of course I will resist, Eleo-chan. Please
step back, it's dangerous.

Mage Relm: I will make you regret spreading the tears of the
dragon.

Thief Nora: As the representative of the Emma Thieves Gang,
I will fight against you who have been rampaging through the
campus!
Clea: I have no intention of letting you escape either.

Loparo Plundering Gang Leader: There's no doubt that Pido
hired them... It feels similar to when we were being chased
by Atu.

Sister Sophia: The battle has come to an end, you should
give up and surrender.

Loparo Plundering Gang Leader: I am the leader of the
plundering gang... I have taken everything that can be
taken, be it money, food, women, or lives.

Loparo Plundering Gang Leader: Even someone like me... I've
never taken a life before!

Sister Eleo: Please stop! Don't do something as reckless as
taking lives!

Loparo Plundering Gang Leader: I'm grateful that we have a
naive monk as our leader. Since we have hostages here, you
can't lay a finger on us, right?

Loparo Plundering Gang Leader: If bluffing won't work, how
about I chop off a finger or two?

Sister Sophia: Let go of Eleo-chan! You already know that
whatever you do is pointless, right?!

Loparo Plundering Gang Leader: I know that! So it shouldn't
be a problem to take the young monk with me, right?
Sister Eleo: Why won't you try to understand each other?

Loparo Plundering Gang Leader: The one who rejected me first
is the goddess that you all hold dear.

Loparo Plundering Gang Leader: During the war, I ended up on
a small island, right in the middle between the Empire and
the neighboring country of Tarasa.

Loparo Plundering Gang Leader: When I looked from afar, it
was strangely large, and as I got closer, I realized it was
a shipwreck and a countless number of corpses.

Loparo Plundering Gang Leader: We prayed desperately every
single day, but nothing changed, nothing happened!

Loparo Plundering Gang Leader: Hey, tell me, do you call
muttering in a safe place 'praying'?

Sister Eleo: As you said, there is no meaning to prayers,
just as you claim.

Sister Eleo: Moreover, it's impossible for reality to change
like that.

Sister Eleo: My prayers are not as grand as you think, just
a small hope that tomorrow will be better than today.

Sister Eleo: And that... is something done not for oneself,
but for someone else.

Sister Eleo: You said you were rejected by the goddess
because you had high expectations of her.

Sister Eleo: After the hero defeated the demon, the three
goddesses left the earth.

Sister Eleo: There is no god in this land. Only humans have
the power to change something.

Sister Eleo: I was taught that not only from the scriptures,
but also from everyone present there.
Sister Sophia: Are you okay? Are you injured!?

Sister Eleo: I will negotiate for Pido-sama to show
leniency.

Leader of the Loparo Plundering Gang: Ah... do as you
please.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

Leader of the Loparo Plundering Gang: Well, it's no match
for Atu from the Imperial Army, but Pido sent you, so there
must be something.

Leader of the Loparo Plundering Gang: Sister Eleo, shall we
continue our conversation?

Sister Eleo: Even in this situation, I want to save
everyone.
Sister Sophia: R-run, Eleo-chan... These guys...

Leader of the Loparo Plundering Gang: Do you want to call us
beasts? Well, maybe you're not entirely wrong.

Leader of the Loparo Plundering Gang: Plundering, arson,
rape, murder, kidnapping... It's a lack of character that
even sealed demons would be astonished by.

Leader of the Loparo Plundering Gang: What's wrong, Sister
Eleo? Are you going to save us? You seem frozen in place.

Leader of the Loparo Plundering Gang: That sister over there
must be really important to the priest-sama.

Leader of the Loparo Plundering Gang: I will take away
everything, from your faith to your life, and plunder it all
right in front of him.

Sister Eleo: I understand... But please, do not lay a hand
on anyone.

Sister Sophia: Run... Th-these guys, they won't keep their
promise...!

Leader of the Loparo Plundering Gang: Pray to the goddess
all you want. By the time this is over, you'll realize it
was all meaningless.

Leader of the Loparo Plundering Gang: Once it's time, I'll
let you know.
Would you like to skip the adult scene?

Do you want to retry the battle? If you choose No, it will
result in a game over.
